<span class="comment"># Complex type hints</span>
<span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">process_data</span>(
    data: Dict[<span class="keyword">str</span>, List[<span class="keyword">int</span>]], 
    threshold: Optional[<span class="keyword">float</span>] = <span class="keyword">None</span>
) -> Tuple[<span class="keyword">int</span>, <span class="keyword">float</span>]:
    total = <span class="keyword">sum</span>(<span class="keyword">sum</span>(values) <span class="keyword">for</span> values <span class="keyword">in</span> data.values())
    avg = total / <span class="keyword">len</span>(data) <span class="keyword">if</span> data <span class="keyword">else</span> <span class="number">0.0</span>
    <span class="keyword">return</span> total, avg

<span class="comment"># Union types</span>
<span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">parse_number</span>(value: Union[<span class="keyword">str</span>, <span class="keyword">int</span>, <span class="keyword">float</span>]) -> <span class="keyword">float</span>:

                <h3>Using if...elif...else</h3>
                <pre><code>score = <span class="number">85</span>

    grade = <span class="string">"A"</span>

<span class="keyword">elif</span> score >= <span class="number">60</span>:

                <h3>One-Line if Statement (Ternary Operator)</h3>
                <pre><code><span class="comment"># Syntax: value_if_true if condition else value_if_false</span>

                <h3>Check Multiple Conditions</h3>
                <pre><code><span class="comment"># Using and/or operators</span>

    <span class="keyword">print</span>(<span class="string">"You can drive"</span>)

<span class="comment"># Using any() and all()</span>

<span class="keyword">if</span> <span class="keyword">all</span>(conditions):
    <span class="keyword">print</span>(<span class="string">"All conditions met"</span>)

    <span class="keyword">print</span>(<span class="string">"At least one positive number"</span>)</code></pre>

                <h2>Structural Pattern Matching (Python 3.10+)</h2>
                <pre><code><span class="comment"># Basic match statement</span>

        <span class="keyword">case</span> <span class="number">200</span>:
            <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="string">"OK"</span>
        <span class="keyword">case</span> <span class="number">404</span>:
            <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="string">"Not Found"</span>
        <span class="keyword">case</span> <span class="number">500</span>:
            <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="string">"Internal Server Error"</span>
        <span class="keyword">case</span> _:
            <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="string">"Unknown status"</span>

<span class="comment"># Pattern matching with conditions</span>
<span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">categorize_number</span>(n):
    <span class="keyword">match</span> n:
        <span class="keyword">case</span> <span class="number">0</span>:
            <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="string">"zero"</span>
        <span class="keyword">case</span> n <span class="keyword">if</span> n > <span class="number">0</span>:
            <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="string">"positive"</span>
        <span class="keyword">case</span> n <span class="keyword">if</span> n < <span class="number">0</span>:
            <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="string">"negative"</span>

<span class="comment"># Matching sequences</span>
<span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">process_command</span>(command):
    <span class="keyword">match</span> command.split():
        <span class="keyword">case</span> [<span class="string">"quit"</span>]:
            <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="string">"Goodbye!"</span>
        <span class="keyword">case</span> [<span class="string">"hello"</span>, name]:
            <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="string">f"Hello, {name}!"</span>
        <span class="keyword">case</span> [<span class="string">"add"</span>, x, y]:
            <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="keyword">int</span>(x) + <span class="keyword">int</span>(y)
        <span class="keyword">case</span> _:
            <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="string">"Unknown command"</span>

<span class="comment"># Matching dictionaries</span>
<span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">process_user</span>(user):
    <span class="keyword">match</span> user:
        <span class="keyword">case</span> {<span class="string">"name"</span>: name, <span class="string">"age"</span>: age} <span class="keyword">if</span> age >= <span class="number">18</span>:
            <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="string">f"{name} is an adult"</span>
        <span class="keyword">case</span> {<span class="string">"name"</span>: name, <span class="string">"age"</span>: age}:
            <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="string">f"{name} is a minor"</span>
        <span class="keyword">case</span> _:
            <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="string">"Invalid user data"</span></code></pre>

                <h3>Decorators</h3>

<span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">timer</span>(func):
    <span class="keyword">import</span> time
    <span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">wrapper</span>(*args, **kwargs):
        start = time.time()
        result = func(*args, **kwargs)
        end = time.time()
        <span class="keyword">print</span>(<span class="string">f"{func.__name__} took {end - start:.4f} seconds"</span>)
        <span class="keyword">return</span> result
    <span class="keyword">return</span> wrapper

<span class="comment">@timer</span>
<span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">slow_function</span>():
    <span class="keyword">import</span> time
    time.sleep(<span class="number">1</span>)
    <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="string">"Done"</span>

<span class="comment"># Decorator with arguments</span>
<span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">repeat</span>(n):
    <span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">decorator</span>(func):
        <span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">wrapper</span>(*args, **kwargs):
            <span class="keyword">for</span> _ <span class="keyword">in</span> <span class="keyword">range</span>(n):
                result = func(*args, **kwargs)
            <span class="keyword">return</span> result
        <span class="keyword">return</span> wrapper
    <span class="keyword">return</span> decorator

<span class="comment">@repeat(3)</span>
<span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">say_hello</span>():
    <span class="keyword">print</span>(<span class="string">"Hello!"</span>)</code></pre>

                <h3>Special Methods (Magic Methods)</h3>
                <pre><code><span class="keyword">class</span> <span class="function">Vector</span>:
    <span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">__init__</span>(self, x, y):
        self.x = x
        self.y = y
    
    <span class="comment"># String representations</span>
    <span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">__str__</span>(self):
        <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="string">f"Vector({self.x}, {self.y})"</span>
    
    <span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">__repr__</span>(self):
        <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="string">f"Vector(x={self.x}, y={self.y})"</span>
    
    <span class="comment"># Arithmetic operations</span>
    <span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">__add__</span>(self, other):
        <span class="keyword">return</span> Vector(self.x + other.x, self.y + other.y)
    
    <span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">__sub__</span>(self, other):
        <span class="keyword">return</span> Vector(self.x - other.x, self.y - other.y)
    
    <span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">__mul__</span>(self, scalar):
        <span class="keyword">return</span> Vector(self.x * scalar, self.y * scalar)
    
    <span class="comment"># Comparison</span>

<span class="keyword">class</span> <span class="function">SingletonMeta</span>(<span class="keyword">type</span>):
    _instances = {}
    
    <span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">__call__</span>(cls, *args, **kwargs):
        <span class="keyword">if</span> cls <span class="keyword">not in</span> cls._instances:

    <span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">__new__</span>(mcs, name, bases, namespace):
        <span class="comment"># Add getter/setter for attributes starting with '_'</span>
        <span class="keyword">for</span> key, value <span class="keyword">in</span> <span class="keyword">list</span>(namespace.items()):
            <span class="keyword">if</span> key.startswith(<span class="string">'_'</span>) <span class="keyword">and not</span> key.startswith(<span class="string">'__'</span>):
                <span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">make_property</span>(attr_name):
                    <span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">getter</span>(self):
                        <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="keyword">getattr</span>(self, attr_name)

                        <span class="keyword">setattr</span>(self, attr_name, value)

                prop_name = key[<span class="number">1</span>:]  <span class="comment"># Remove leading underscore</span>
                namespace[prop_name] = make_property(key)
        
        <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="keyword">super</span>().__new__(mcs, name, bases, namespace)</code></pre>

                <pre><code><span class="comment"># Descriptor protocol</span>
<span class="keyword">class</span> <span class="function">ValidatedAttribute</span>:
    <span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">__init__</span>(self, validator):
        self.validator = validator

    <span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">__get__</span>(self, obj, objtype=<span class="keyword">None</span>):

    <span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">__set__</span>(self, obj, value):
        self.validator(value)
        self.data[<span class="keyword">id</span>(obj)] = value
    
    <span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">__delete__</span>(self, obj):
        <span class="keyword">del</span> self.data[<span class="keyword">id</span>(obj)]

    <span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">validate_name</span>(value):

            <span class="keyword">raise</span> ValueError(<span class="string">"Name must be a non-empty string"</span>)

    name = ValidatedAttribute(validate_name)

        self.age = age

    <span class="keyword">return</span> result

        x = self.fc2(x)
        <span class="keyword">return</span> x

    <span class="keyword">for</span> epoch <span class="keyword">in</span> <span class="keyword">range</span>(epochs):
        running_loss = <span class="number">0.0</span>
        <span class="keyword">for</span> inputs, labels <span class="keyword">in</span> dataloader:
            <span class="comment"># Zero gradients</span>
            optimizer.zero_grad()
            
            <span class="comment"># Forward pass</span>
            outputs = model(inputs)
            loss = criterion(outputs, labels)
            
            <span class="comment"># Backward pass</span>
            loss.backward()
            optimizer.step()
            
            running_loss += loss.item()
        
        <span class="keyword">print</span>(<span class="string">f"Epoch {epoch+1}, Loss: {running_loss/len(dataloader):.4f}"</span>)</code></pre>

                <h3>CNN Example</h3>
                <pre><code><span class="comment"># Convolutional Neural Network</span>

        <span class="keyword">super</span>(CNN, self).__init__()
        <span class="comment"># Convolutional layers</span>
        self.conv1 = nn.Conv2d(in_channels=<span class="number">3</span>, out_channels=<span class="number">32</span>, 
                               kernel_size=<span class="number">3</span>, padding=<span class="number">1</span>)
        self.conv2 = nn.Conv2d(<span class="number">32</span>, <span class="number">64</span>, <span class="number">3</span>, padding=<span class="number">1</span>)
        self.conv3 = nn.Conv2d(<span class="number">64</span>, <span class="number">128</span>, <span class="number">3</span>, padding=<span class="number">1</span>)
        
        <span class="comment"># Pooling layer</span>
        self.pool = nn.MaxPool2d(kernel_size=<span class="number">2</span>, stride=<span class="number">2</span>)
        
        <span class="comment"># Fully connected layers</span>
        self.fc1 = nn.Linear(<span class="number">128</span> * <span class="number">4</span> * <span class="number">4</span>, <span class="number">512</span>)
        self.fc2 = nn.Linear(<span class="number">512</span>, num_classes)
        
        self.dropout = nn.Dropout(<span class="number">0.5</span>)
    
    <span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">forward</span>(self, x):
        <span class="comment"># Conv layers with ReLU and pooling</span>
        x = self.pool(F.relu(self.conv1(x)))
        x = self.pool(F.relu(self.conv2(x)))
        x = self.pool(F.relu(self.conv3(x)))
        
        <span class="comment"># Flatten</span>
        x = x.view(-<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">128</span> * <span class="number">4</span> * <span class="number">4</span>)
        
        <span class="comment"># Fully connected layers</span>
        x = F.relu(self.fc1(x))
        x = self.dropout(x)
        x = self.fc2(x)
        
        <span class="keyword">return</span> x

    <span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="function">__getitem__</span>(self, idx):

        label = self.labels[idx]
        
        <span class="keyword">if</span> self.transform:
            sample = self.transform(sample)
        
        <span class="keyword">return</span> sample, label</code></pre>
